Jax Deluca
Jax Deluca is the Media Arts Director at the National Endowment for the Arts. Through this work, she oversees the Endowments national grant portfolio and field-building initiatives to support media art activities, including film, video, audio, creative code, immersive technology, and other forms of electronic media art. With a background in expanded cinema, sound, and performance, she brings experience as a non-profit arts administrator, arts educator, independent artist, and a DIY arts supporter to this federal position serving the media arts field.
